p
\sum_{i=1}^{8}n_i=21
\hat p
p
\mathcal L(n;p)=\prod_{i=1}^{8}(n_i+1)(1-p)^{n_i}p^2=\left(p^2\right)^8(1-p)^{\sum_{i=1}^{8} n_i}\prod_{i=1}^{8}(n_i+1)
\ln \mathcal L(n;p)=16\ln p+\sum_{i=1}^{8} n_i\cdot\ln(1-p)+\sum_{i=1}^{n}\ln(n_i+1)
0=\frac{16}{p}-\frac{1}{1-p}\sum_{i=1}^{8} n_i
\hat p=\frac{16}{16+\sum_{i=1}^{8} n_i}
\hat p= \frac{16}{16+21}=\frac{16}{37}
